  },
  {
    icon: '🧠',
    title: 'Understands Flooring Enquiries',
    text: "When a caller says 'I need LVT in the kitchen and hallway' or 'can you lay engineered oak over underfloor heating,' the AI understands what they mean. It captures room sizes, flooring preferences, subfloor concerns, and whether they need uplift of existing flooring."
  },
  {
    icon: '🚨',
    title: 'Escalates Urgent Jobs',
    text: "A care home with vinyl lifting in a corridor. A restaurant with tiles cracking before an inspection. The AI recognises emergency language and escalates immediately — reaching your mobile first, then our human operators. Routine domestic measure-up requests are handled as standard leads."
  },
  {
    icon: '🕐',
    title: 'Covers Evenings and Weekends',
    text: "Homeowners browse flooring samples on Saturday mornings and ring fitters between 6pm and 9pm on weeknights. Those are prime enquiry windows and you are often driving home or eating dinner. The AI catches every one."
  },
  {
    icon: '📋',
    title: 'Detailed Lead Summaries',
    text: "Every call is summarised with the caller's name, number, location, flooring type they want, number of rooms, and any specific requirements like underfloor heating compatibility or subfloor preparation. You call back fully informed."
  },
  {
