    title: 'Your Business Name, Your Greeting',
    text: "The AI answers as your flooring business. 'Good morning, thank you for calling Premier Floors, how can I help?' Callers hear a professional greeting that matches your brand — not a generic answering service."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What does the AI say when a flooring customer calls?",
    answer: "It greets the caller with your business name and has a natural conversation to understand what they need. For flooring businesses, it asks about the type of flooring (LVT, engineered wood, carpet, vinyl), which rooms are involved, approximate sizes if the caller knows them, whether existing flooring needs removing, and captures their contact details and availability for a measure-up."
  },
  {
    question: "Can it handle calls about different flooring types?",
    answer: "Yes — carpet, LVT, engineered wood, laminate, vinyl, safety flooring, carpet tiles, and specialist products like Karndean or Amtico. The AI captures whatever the caller describes and notes any brand preferences. It does not try to advise on products — that is your job when you call back."
  },
  {
    question: "What if a commercial client calls about a large contract?",
    answer: "The AI handles commercial enquiries the same way — capturing the facility type, square meterage if mentioned, the flooring specification, timeline, and contact details. Whether it is a school, office, medical practice, or retail unit, the lead summary gives you everything you need to follow up professionally."
  },
  {
    question: "How many minutes of phone time do I get?",
    answer: `The Core plan includes ${pricing.tiers.core.minutes} minutes per month — enough for most sole trader fitters handling domestic work. The Core plan gives you ${pricing.tiers.core.minutes} minutes for busier flooring companies. Additional minutes are 20p each with no cap or penalty.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I still answer calls myself when I'm available?",
    answer: "Yes. The AI only activates when you are unavailable — on a job, driving, or after hours. When you are in the showroom or between installations, calls come through to you as normal. You control when the AI picks up."
  },
  {
    question: "How does Rapid Receptionist protect customer data?",
    answer: "All data is managed under UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018. Names, addresses, phone numbers, and job descriptions are encrypted in transit and at rest, stored on UK and EU servers, and shared only with you. We never sell or repurpose enquiry data. Full details are in our privacy policy."
